getTimeConstraint

public java.util.Date getTimeConstraint()
                                 throws java.lang.IllegalStateException
Returns time constraint.

The time constraint is in the following format: "yyyyMMddHHmmSS.tZ", which is the GeneralizedTime authorized by ITU-T in Coordinated Universal Time (UTC) format. For example, to indicate 1:20 pm on May the 31st, 1999 for UTC, one would write: "19990531132000.0Z".

Specified by:
getTimeConstraint in interface javax.oss.fm.monitor.QueryByFilterableAttributesValue
